  <static seed="27" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionsCalculation/EquivalentFraction10.pg">
    <statement><p>Find an equivalent fraction to <m>\frac{1}{9}</m> with denominator <m>36</m>.</p>
<p><fillin characters="8" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{4}{36}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>From <m>9</m> to <m>36</m>, we multiplied by <m>36\div9=4</m>.</p>
<p>For a fraction, when we multiply the same number in both the numerator and denominator, the fraction<rsq/>s value doesn<rsq/>t change. We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{9}=\frac{1\cdot4}{9\cdot4} = \frac{4}{36} }</m></p>
</solution>
